4 (c) The individual takes the weapon without the consent of the
5 peace officer or corrections officer.
6 (d) The peace officer or corrections officer is authorized by
7 his or her the peace officer's or corrections officer's employer to
8 carry the weapon in the line of duty.
9 (2) An Except as otherwise provided in subsection (3), an
10 individual who takes a firearm from the lawful possession of a
11 peace officer or a corrections officer is guilty of a felony
12 punishable by imprisonment for not more than 10 years or a fine of
13 not more than $5,000.00, or both, if all of the following
14 circumstances exist at the time the firearm is taken:
15 (a) The individual knows or has reason to believe the person
16 from whom the firearm is taken is a peace officer or a corrections
17 officer.
18 (b) The peace officer or corrections officer is performing his
