16 (4) (3) This section does not prohibit an individual from
17 being charged with, convicted of, or punished for any other
18 violation of law that is committed by that individual while
19 violating this section.
20 (5) (4) A term of imprisonment imposed for a violation of this
21 section may run consecutively to any term of imprisonment imposed
22 for another violation arising from the same transaction.
23 (6) (5) As used in this section:
24 (a) "Corrections officer" means a prison or jail guard or
25 other employee of a jail or a state or federal correctional
26 facility, who performs duties involving the transportation, care,
27 custody, or supervision of prisoners.
28 (b) "Peace officer" means 1 or more of the following:
29 (i) A police officer of this state or a political subdivision
